Phillip HOLLANDER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES, Appellee. No. 4640. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Nov. 2, 1931. Irving H. Lewis, of Trenton, N. J., and Benjamin M. Golder, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. Phillip Forman, U. S. Atty., of Trenton, N. J., and John Grimshaw, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., of Paterson, N. J.

Before BUFFINGTON, WOOLLEY, and DAYIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon due consideration had, finding no error in the record, the judgment below is affirmed.
